The stolen mace taken from the Senate Chamber has just been returned to the National Assembly by the police. Clerk of the National Assembly, Sani Omolori received the Mace from the Deputy Inspector General of Police in charge of operations at the Force Headquarters, DIG Habila Joshak alongside the Divisional Police Officer of the National Assembly, Sulu Gambari. The mace was later taken to the office of the Clerk of the National Assembly.  Meanwhile, six suspects have been arrested by the police for stealing the Mace. A top police officer confirmed this to journalists with pictures as evidence of the arrest. He said the suspects would soon be charged to court.